        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 18928] Missing pieces in the C API for environments*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18928>\n\n--- Comment #26 from Lionel Henry (<mailto:lionel.hry@gmail.com|lionel.hry@gmail.com>) ---\nCreated attachment 3634\n  --&gt; <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3634&amp;action=edit>\nFix R_DotsExist with missing dots\n\nRegarding scoping in the dots API, good question. The current implementation\nwith `inherits = TRUE` is aligned with how we use it in rlang, but I agree it's\nnot ideal because ambiguous.\n\nIf we hardcode `inherits = FALSE`, then it's more in line with the environment\nbindings API. We can implement the inherit behaviour ourselves with a search.\nArguments for not having `inherits`:\n\n- It would be a bit weird with the accessor variants.\n\n- Another argument pointed out by Davis is that it forces you to first find the\nrelevant frame, then access it, and that prevents reclimbing multiple times\nacross multiple uses of e.g. `R_DotsElt()`.",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
