                                "text": "lionel.hry@gmail.com"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") ---\nCreated attachment 3634\n  --> "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3634&amp;action=edit",
                                "text": "https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3634&action=edit"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\nFix R_DotsExist with missing dots\n\nRegarding scoping in the dots API, good question. The current implementation\nwith "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "inherits = TRUE",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " is aligned with how we use it in rlang, but I agree it's\nnot ideal because ambiguous.\n\nIf we hardcode "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "inherits = FALSE",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ", then it's more in line with the environment\nbindings API. We can implement the inherit behaviour ourselves with a search.\nArguments for not having "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "inherits",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ":\n\n- It would be a bit weird with the accessor variants.\n\n- Another argument pointed out by Davis is that it forces you to first find the\nrelevant frame, then access it, and that prevents reclimbing multiple times\nacross multiple uses of e.g. "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "R_DotsElt()",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
